# The Unsealing: Why the Wise Understand and the Foolish Dismiss

## A Call to Test, Not Reject

---

## The Time Has Come

**Daniel 12:4** — *"But thou, O Daniel, shut up the words, and seal the book, even to the time of the end: many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall be increased."*

For centuries, the book was sealed. Not because the words weren't written — they were always there. Not because the characteristics weren't given — they were laid out plainly. But because the time had not yet come for them to be fully understood.

The seal was temporal, not textual.

Daniel was told to "shut up the words" — to close and preserve them — **until the time of the end.** The prophecies would remain, waiting for the generation that would see their fulfillment. Waiting for the moment when the characteristics given in Scripture could finally be matched to observable, verifiable reality.

That time has come.

---

## What "Knowledge Increased" Means

When Daniel 12:4 speaks of knowledge increasing, it does not merely refer to technological advancement or information access — though these are signs in themselves. It refers to **prophetic knowledge**: the capacity to understand what was previously sealed.

Consider what is now possible:

- The complete text of Scripture, cross-referenced and searchable
- The ability to trace a single characteristic across sixty-six books instantly
- Historical records verifying the fulfillment of past prophecies
- Real-time observation of geopolitical developments matching prophetic descriptions
- Tools capable of organizing, auditing, and presenting the biblical testimony systematically

The very capacity to build a forensic audit of prophecy — to lay characteristic beside fulfillment, to test the methodology against the track record, to present the evidence comprehensively — this capacity did not exist in previous generations.

**The seal is being lifted.**

The wise of past generations saw in part. They understood the broad outlines. But they could not see what we now see, because the players were not yet on the stage. The second beast had not fully risen. The infrastructure for universal economic control did not exist. The deadly wound had not yet healed. Israel was not yet back in the land.

Now all of this is visible. Now the characteristics can be matched. Now the audit can be performed.

This is the unsealing. This is knowledge increased. This is the time of the end.

---

## The Methodology: Characteristics First, Names Revealed

God has always worked the same way.

He does not give the names of future powers in advance — this would allow those powers to suppress or alter the prophecy. Instead, He gives **characteristics**: descriptive markers that accumulate across Scripture, waiting to be matched to reality when the time comes.

This methodology is not speculation. It is the **proven biblical pattern**.

### The Track Record

**Cyrus** — Named by Isaiah 150 years before his birth (Isaiah 44:28–45:1). The characteristics were given: he would decree Jerusalem rebuilt, he would subdue nations, the two-leaved gates would open before him. When the time came, Cyrus appeared and fulfilled every characteristic. The name was revealed in history.

**The Four Kingdoms** — Daniel 2 gave the characteristics: gold, silver, brass, iron, then division. No names were given in the original vision. But Daniel 8 later identified Medo-Persia and Greece explicitly, and history revealed Rome as the fourth. The characteristics came first; the names followed.

**The Messiah** — Born in Bethlehem (Micah 5:2). Born of a virgin (Isaiah 7:14). Betrayed for thirty pieces of silver (Zechariah 11:12-13). Hands and feet pierced (Psalm 22:16). Buried with the rich (Isaiah 53:9). Every characteristic was given centuries in advance. When Jesus came, He fulfilled them all. The name was revealed in history.

**Babylon's Fall** — The handwriting on the wall gave the characteristics: kingdom numbered, weighed, divided, given to Medes and Persians (Daniel 5:25-28). That same night, Belshazzar was slain and Darius the Mede took the kingdom. The characteristics came first; the names followed within hours.

This is not one isolated instance. This is the **consistent pattern** throughout Scripture. God gives the blueprint. History fills in the names. The wise recognize the match.

---

## The Division: Wise and Foolish

**Daniel 12:9-10** — *"And he said, Go thy way, Daniel: for the words are closed up and sealed till the time of the end. Many shall be purified, and made white, and tried; but the wicked shall do wickedly: and none of the wicked shall understand; but the wise shall understand."*

Here is the sobering reality: when the seal is lifted, not everyone will see.

The same information will be available to all. The same characteristics. The same methodology. The same track record. The same forensic audit. But two groups will respond in opposite ways:

**The wise shall understand.**

**The wicked shall not understand.**

Notice carefully: the text does not say the wicked *cannot* understand — as though they lack the intellectual capacity. It says they *shall not* understand. And it connects this directly to their moral state: "the wicked shall do wickedly."

Their failure to understand is not intellectual. It is moral. They do not see because they do not wish to see. Seeing would require changing. Understanding would require submitting. So they close their eyes.

---

## Why People Dismiss

**Matthew 13:13-15** — *"Therefore speak I to them in parables: because they seeing see not; and hearing they hear not, neither do they understand. And in them is fulfilled the prophecy of Esaias, which saith, By hearing ye shall hear, and shall not understand; and seeing ye shall see, and shall not perceive: For this people's heart is waxed gross, and their ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes they have closed; lest at any time they should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and should understand with their heart, and should be converted, and I should heal them."*

Jesus explains the mechanism: **"their eyes they have closed."**

This is active, not passive. This is choice, not incapacity. The information is available. The evidence is presented. The methodology is sound. But they close their eyes — **lest** they should see, and hear, and understand, and be converted.

Conversion is the threat. Change is the danger. If they see, they must respond. If they understand, they must act. So they refuse to look.

**Proverbs 1:7** — *"The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction."*

The fool does not lack access to wisdom. He **despises** it. He dismisses it without examination. He mocks it without engagement. He rejects it without testing.

This is the spirit of the age: dismissal without investigation. Mockery without study. Rejection without reason.

And this too is prophesied:

**2 Peter 3:3-4** — *"Knowing this first, that there shall come in the last days scoffers, walking after their own lusts, And saying, Where is the promise of his coming? for since the fathers fell asleep, all things continue as they were from the beginning of the creation."*

Scoffers. Walking after their own lusts. Assuming uniformity — that because things have continued, they will continue. Willfully ignorant of prior divine interventions.

The dismissal is itself a sign.

---

## The Call: Test, Do Not Dismiss

**1 Thessalonians 5:20-21** — *"Despise not prophesyings. Prove all things; hold fast that which is good."*

Scripture does not command blind acceptance. But neither does it permit blind rejection. The command is to **prove** — to test, to examine, to verify.

This is the call:

**Do not dismiss. Test.**

The methodology is presented: Scripture interprets Scripture. Characteristics identification. The Bible defines its own terms.

The track record is established: Cyrus, the four kingdoms, the Messiah, Babylon's fall. Every prophecy that has been fulfilled followed this pattern.

The current application is audited: The first beast's characteristics. The second beast's characteristics. The mark. The three-part Babylon. The Euphrates system. The timeline markers.

Everything is laid out for examination. Nothing is hidden. Nothing requires secret knowledge. The evidence is public. The Scripture references are cited. The methodology is transparent.

**Test it.**

Compare the characteristics given in Revelation 13 with the attributes of the Papacy. Do they match or not?

Compare the characteristics of the second beast with the attributes of America. Do they match or not?

Compare the biblical definition of "dried up" with the function of the Euphrates-Hormuz system. Does the pattern hold or not?

Compare the track record of fulfilled prophecy with the methodology being applied. Is it consistent or not?

This is not a demand for agreement. This is an invitation to verification. The wise will test. The foolish will dismiss without testing.

Which will you be?

---

## The Danger of Dismissal

**Hosea 4:6** — *"My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge: because thou hast rejected knowledge, I will also reject thee."*

The destruction is not from lack of availability. It is from **rejection**. The knowledge was offered. It was refused. And the consequence follows.

**Proverbs 29:18** — *"Where there is no vision, the people perish."*

When prophetic understanding is absent — whether because it is not given or because it is rejected — the people perish. They do not see what is coming. They are overtaken as by a thief. They are caught unaware.

But it does not have to be this way:

**1 Thessalonians 5:4-6** — *"But ye, brethren, are not in darkness, that that day should overtake you as a thief. Ye are all the children of light, and the children of the day: we are not of the night, nor of darkness. Therefore let us not sleep, as do others; but let us watch and be sober."*

The children of light are **not** overtaken. They see the day approaching. They recognize the season. They watch and are sober.

This is the choice before every person who encounters this material:

- **Dismiss without testing** — and join the company of scoffers, the willfully ignorant, those whose hearts are waxed gross and whose eyes are closed.

- **Test honestly** — and discover whether the characteristics match, whether the methodology holds, whether the seal has truly been lifted in this generation.

The evidence is available. The knowledge has increased. The book is being unsealed.

**What will you do with it?**

---

## The Heart of the Matter

**Matthew 24:37-39** — *"But as the days of Noe were, so shall also the coming of the Son of man be. For as in the days that were before the flood they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, until the day that Noe entered into the ark, And knew not until the flood came, and took them all away; so shall also the coming of the Son of man be."*

Noah preached. Noah built. Noah warned. The evidence was visible — a massive ark under construction. The message was clear — judgment was coming.

And they dismissed it. They continued eating and drinking. They continued as though nothing would change. **And knew not until the flood came.**

They did not know — not because they couldn't, but because they wouldn't.

The ark is being built again. The message is being proclaimed again. The characteristics are being matched to reality again. The track record is being presented again.

**Luke 21:28** — *"And when these things begin to come to pass, then look up, and lift up your heads; for your redemption draweth nigh."*

For those with eyes to see: this is not a message of doom. This is a message of hope. Redemption draws nigh. The King is coming. The long night is almost over.

But you must be willing to look. You must be willing to test. You must be willing to see.

---

## Conclusion: The Seal Is Lifted

The prophecies were always there. The characteristics were always given. The methodology was always sound.

But the book was sealed until the time of the end.

Now the seal is being lifted. The players are on the stage. The infrastructure is visible. The characteristics can be matched. The audit can be performed.

**Daniel 12:10** — *"Many shall be purified, and made white, and tried; but the wicked shall do wickedly: and none of the wicked shall understand; but the wise shall understand."*

The wise will understand. They will test. They will compare. They will see the match between characteristic and fulfillment. They will recognize the season.

The wicked will not understand. They will dismiss. They will mock. They will close their eyes lest they should see and be converted.

The same sun that melts the wax hardens the clay. The same evidence that opens the eyes of the wise confirms the blindness of the foolish.

This is the time. This is the unsealing. This is the call.

**Test, do not dismiss.**

**Watch, do not sleep.**

**Look up — your redemption draws nigh.**

---

**Amos 3:7** — *"Surely the Lord GOD will do nothing, but he revealeth his secret unto his servants the prophets."*

**2 Peter 1:19-21** — *"We have also a more sure word of prophecy; whereunto ye do well that ye take heed, as unto a light that shineth in a dark place, until the day dawn, and the day star arise in your hearts: Knowing this first, that no prophecy of the scripture is of any private interpretation. For the prophecy came not in old time by the will of man: but holy men of God spake as they were moved by the Holy Ghost."*

The light shines in a dark place. Take heed. The day star is about to arise.

